Description & usage

The UU Capability Model (UUCM) is an anchor for assessing strategic importance, maturity, business operational pain points, capital investment, and organizational structure. 

The UUCM supports the development of strategies by viewing the business as a collection of capabilities that can be adjusted in response to the demands of the business environment. 

Business Stakeholders, Enterprise Architects, and Technology Strategists can use the model as a reference to engage in discussion regarding for example business effectiveness,  needs, and challenges or technology decisions.
